Shenzhen , May 19 -LRB- Xinhua -RRB- -- The second 66-man contingent of the advance party of People 's Liberation Army -LRB- PLA -RRB- soldiers to be stationed in the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region -LRB- SAR -RRB- left Shenzhen for Hong Kong today in accordance with the agreement of the Sino - British Joint Liaison Group .
There are 43 days remaining until the Chinese government resumes the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong .
A solemn ceremony was held for the advance party at 11 : 00 this morning with a military band playing the national anthem of the People 's Republic of China .
An honor guard made up of ground , naval , and air forces of the PLA were on hand to see the advance party off .
Major - General Xiong Ziren , the political commissar of the PLA Troops to be stationed in Hong Kong SAR , read off the names of the 66-member contingent .
This was followed by a speech from Major - General Liu Zhenwu , the commander of the PLA Hong Kong Troops , who called on the advance party to carry on the fine traditions of the PLA , and to perform the sacred duties entrusted to them by the country and people to the fullest .
Lu Zhiwen , deputy brigade commander of the infantry group of the PLA Hong Kong Troops , said on behalf of the advance party that they are determined to live up to the expectations of the country and the people and make all the preparations for the stationing of the PLA Hong Kong Troops .
The second contingent will , together with the first 40-member contingent sent earlier , make necessary preparations for the PLA Troops ' formal stationing in the Hong Kong SAR beginning from zero hour on July 1 to assume the responsibility of defence affairs .
The 196-member advance party assigned to Hong Kong is to be sent in three groups .
The final 90-member contingent of the advance party will enter Hong Kong on May 30 .
